      <section id="id5095899">
        <title>To do creative writing with words that imitate their sound and begin with the same sound [LO 4.3.1]</title>
        <para id="id4522156">WRITING POETRY</para>
        <para id="id3341036">1. Write a short poem about your favourite musician or group. </para>
        <para id="id7808801">Try to use words that imitate the sound of the object you are writing about (e.g. the crashing cymbals; the whining guitar). This is called <emphasis effect="bold">onomatopoeia</emphasis>. (What a word!) Look at the poem about the gypsies again and try to find some “sound-imitating” words. Also try to use <emphasis effect="bold">alliteration</emphasis> (words next to or close to each other start with the same sound, e.g. Tiny Tim). Your educator will guide you.</para>
