      <section id="id6921822">
        <title>Activity 2</title>
        <para id="id7426757">Discuss aspects of poetry such as metre, rhyme, poetic devices such as alliteration, assonance, simile, metaphor, etc.</para>
        <para id="id7367070">Punctuation: Why is it necessary? Makes meaning clear, enhances mood/register, etc. Show how different ways of punctuating a sentence can change its meaning.</para>
        <section id="id1739277">
          <title>Activity 3</title>
          <para id="id4200575">Teach the rules for contracting words.</para>
          <list id="id1425904" list-type="bulleted">
            <item>e.g. did not = didn’t (the ‘ replaces the missing letters)</item>
            <item>e.g. Peter’s ball… (the ‘ shows that the subject is not a plural, but is showing ownership.</item>
          </list>
          <para id="id7762272">Activity 4</para>
          <para id="id6808120">Time line: link up with other learning area (History) – explain what a time line is, if necessary.</para>
        </section>
